cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.CE, cs.DB 

This paper discusses the implementation of a patient-reported outcome (PRO) instrument in a real-world behavioral healthcare setting and the use of data mining to analyze the outcomes. The paper also discusses the potential use of PROs as the basis for next-generation clinical decision support tools and personalized treatment approaches. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CY (Computers and Society) as the paper discusses the use of technology in healthcare. The second likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the paper discusses the use of data mining to analyze the outcomes. The third likely category is cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) as the paper discusses the implementation factors and clinician perceptions. The fourth likely category is cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) as the paper discusses the predictive modeling of outcomes. The fifth likely category is cs.DB (Databases) as the paper discusses the use of direct client feedback measures and their potential use as the basis for next-generation clinical decision support tools.
